@@ -84,6 +84,19 @@ Cause: the CI-fix phase exhausted its attempts. Fix: inspect `reviews/ci-blocked
 
 Cause: a review phase failed or protected-file tampering was detected. Fix: inspect `task.md`, `logs/`, and `reviews/`, clear with `hive markers clear <folder> --name REVIEW_ERROR`, then re-run.
 
+### `REVIEW_ERROR` … `claude stop hook did not signal completion`
+
+Cause: tmux Claude finished work (or exited) but the Stop hook never wrote `task.folder/.done`, so older Hive builds timed out the `:exit_code_only` wait and stamped `phase=fix reason=fix_failed` with that exact message. Current Hive treats clean session death / idle ready-prompt as success (WARN `claude_completion_fallback`) when evidence holds; the daemon healer also bounded-retries this exact marker.
+
+Fix:
+
+1. Inspect worktree commits, `reviews/`, and `events.jsonl` before clearing.
+2. Prefer letting the daemon healer clear the exact stop-hook message, or manually:
+   `hive markers clear <slug> --name REVIEW_ERROR --project <project>`
+3. `hive run <slug> --project <project>` to re-enter `6-review`.
+
+Workaround on unfixed versions: set `claude.mode: headless` (do not auto-revert configs). Full RCA and recovery notes: `docs/notes/claude-tmux-launch-mode.md`.
+
 ### `reviewer_tampered`, `triage_tampered`, or `fix_tampered`
 
 Cause: an agent changed a protected file such as `plan.md`, `worktree.yml`, or `task.md` during a phase that must not touch it. Fix: inspect the worktree, restore the protected file from git if needed, clear the error marker, and re-run.
