@@ -137,3 +137,125 @@ the runtime can override them in the calling shell:
 
 Legacy `HIVE_BRAINSTORM_TMUX_*` names are still honored as fallbacks for
 one release while projects migrate from the old brainstorm-only runtime.
+
+## Stop-hook completion (RCA + fallback) — 2026-06-29
+
+### Failure mode observed
+
+Tmux Claude spawns that use `status_mode: :exit_code_only` (review fix,
+execute implementer, CI-fix) wait on the Stop-hook sentinel
+`task.folder/.done` via `ClaudeLauncher.wait_for_done_signal`. When Claude
+finishes useful work and the process/session ends cleanly—or returns to the
+idle ready prompt—but the Stop hook never writes `.done` (or writes it too
+late), Hive timed out with:
+
+```text
+claude stop hook did not signal completion
+```
+
+Review then stamped terminal `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed`
+with that exact message (observed 2026-06-29 on tasks 58/PR #622, 287/PR
+#623, 288/PR #624). `agent_end … phase complete` still fires from the
+review ensure path and must **not** be treated as success evidence alone.
+
+### Architectural root cause (primary)
+
+**Tmux `:exit_code_only` made the Stop hook mandatory, while headless treats
+process exit as completion.** Headless `Hive::Agent#handle_exit` returns
+`:ok` on exit code 0 without requiring `.done`. The tmux wait path did not
+mirror that contract: unlike `wait_for_expected_output` (artifact + ready
+prompt / session-death checks), `wait_for_done_signal` only polled
+`.done` until deadline.
+
+### Contributing factors (checked)
+
+| Factor | Status |
+|--------|--------|
+| Installer dual-writes settings to task folder + worktree cwd, both with `HIVE_TASK_STAGE_DIR=<task.folder>` | Correct; hardened with `mkdir -p` stage dir at install |
+| Hook script writes `result.json` then `touch .done` under absolute stage dir | Correct; hardened with `mkdir -p` so missing stage dir cannot abort before `.done` |
+| Settings backup/restore / 0o444 rewrite | Existing contract; not the primary failure mode |
+| Cleanup deleting `.done` mid-wait | Cleanup runs only in `with_shared_session` ensure **after** wait |
+| Claude Code Stop hook not firing on idle turn end / session death | **Residual upstream risk** — not deterministically reproducible in CI; mitigated by fallback |
+
+Most likely production failure sequence:
+
+1. Fix spawn uses `status_mode: :exit_code_only` → `wait_for_done_signal`.
+2. Claude completes and exits (or idles at ready prompt); Stop hook never
+   fires (upstream TUI/session lifecycle).
+3. Deadline → `{ status: :timeout, error_message: "claude stop hook did not signal completion" }`.
+4. `agent_failed?` → `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed`.
+
+### Fix shipped
+
+1. **Signaling hardening** — `stop_hook.sh` and `StopHookInstaller` always
+   ensure the stage directory exists; installer sentinel paths remain the
+   same absolute task-folder paths `ClaudeLauncher.done_path` /
+   `result_path` poll.
+2. **Shared completion fallback** — `wait_for_done_signal` treats clean
+   session death or idle ready-prompt (after a min elapsed guard) as
+   success with `completion_via: :fallback`, emits WARN
+   `claude_completion_fallback` (Events + log line). Limit walls, crashes,
+   and still-running sessions without ready idle still hard-fail.
+3. **Review-fix evidence gate** — review fix passes a
+   `completion_evidence` predicate requiring escalations artifact, no open
+   escalation checkboxes, readable worktree, and commit / dirty / explicit
+   no-change evidence. Post-spawn reclassification covers late evidence.
+4. **Healer backstop** — `StaleAgentHealer` still auto-clears the exact
+   stop-hook `fix_failed` message (bounded). Prefer in-path completion so
+   the healer is rarely needed.
+
+### Mode policy
+
+- **`claude.mode: headless` remains the recommended workaround** on versions
+  **without** this fix. Do **not** auto-revert operator config.
+- After this fix is released and verified in your environment, **tmux is
+  supported again**; operators may switch `claude.mode` back to `tmux`
+  manually.
+- This change does **not** rewrite local `.hive-state/config.yml` defaults.
+
+### Recovery of stuck stop-hook `REVIEW_ERROR` rows
+
+**Automatic:** Daemon `StaleAgentHealer` clears markers matching exactly:
+
+```text
+REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed message="claude stop hook did not signal completion"
+```
+
+Generic `fix_failed` messages stay manual. After clear, re-entry requeues
+review; if `reviews/fix-success-NN.md` already exists the pass advances;
+otherwise Phase 4 may re-run (inspect worktree/PR first to avoid churn).
+
+**Manual (inspect first, never silent multi-task wipe):**
+
+```sh
+# 1. Inspect evidence
+#    - task.md marker text (exact stop-hook message?)
+#    - events.jsonl for agent_end / claude_completion_fallback
+#    - reviews/escalations-NN.md, reviews/fix-success-NN.md
+#    - git log / status on the feature worktree
+#    - PR state if already opened
+
+hive markers clear <slug-or-folder> --name REVIEW_ERROR --project <project>
+# optional tighter match:
+# hive markers clear <slug> --name REVIEW_ERROR --project <project> \
+#   --match-attr phase=fix,reason=fix_failed
+
+hive run <slug> --project <project>   # re-enter 6-review
+```
+
+**Named stuck tasks (2026-06-29):** 58 / PR #622, 287 / PR #623, 288 / PR #624 —
+for each: confirm marker text is the exact stop-hook message, confirm
+commits/PR already contain the intended fix, clear only that task's
+`REVIEW_ERROR`, re-run review so Phase 4 is skipped when
+`fix-success-NN.md` is present or re-evaluated when missing.
+
+### Related env tunables
+
+- `HIVE_CLAUDE_TMUX_DONE_FALLBACK_MIN_ELAPSED_SEC` (default `2.0`) — minimum
+  wall time after prompt send before **session-death** fallback may fire
+  (guards instant-crash false positives).
+- `HIVE_CLAUDE_TMUX_DONE_FALLBACK_READY_PROMPT_MIN_ELAPSED_SEC` (default `15.0`) —
+  longer idle required before **ready-prompt** fallback (guards ready-before-work
+  on execute/ci_fix, which have no evidence gate).
+- `HIVE_CLAUDE_TMUX_DONE_FALLBACK_READY_PROMPT_STREAK` (default `3`) — consecutive
+  ready-prompt polls required before ready-prompt fallback.
